      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Loan interest is calculated based on the remaining principal balance, meaning you pay no interest on the portion used for capital gain. In an amortizing loan, a significant portion of your initial payments goes toward interest rather than reducing the principal, which creates the feeling that your balance isn't moving. Over time, as the principal decreases, less interest accrues each month, causing a larger share of your payment to pay off the principal and ultimately speeding up the payoff.",
